Step 1: Calculate Gross Profit Margin.
• From the income statement:
 – Gross Profit = 2,272,433.90 
 – Total Revenue = 3,956,433.90
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100
 = (2,272,433.90 / 3,956,433.90) × 100 
 ≈ 57.45%

Step 2: Calculate Cash Flow to Debt Ratio.
• From the cash flow statement:
 – Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -1,182,491.05
• From the balance sheet:
 – Accounts Payable = 302,000.00 
 – Taxes Payable = 197,821.72 
 – Total Debt (Current Liabilities) = 302,000.00 + 197,821.72 = 499,821.72
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Debt)
 = -1,182,491.05 / 499,821.72 
 ≈ -2.37

Thus, the answer is as follows:

{"solution": {"Gross Profit Margin": "57.45%", "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-2.37"}}
